===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|lepen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|hleapan|hlēapan}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|hlaupanan|lang=gem-pro}} (compare Dutch {{term|lopen|lang=nl}} ‘to stroll, go for a walk’, German {{term|laufen|lang=de}} ‘to run’, Danish {{term|løbe|lang=en}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} (compare Lithuanian {{term|šlùbti|lang=lt}} ‘to become lame’, {{term|klùbti|lang=lt}} ‘to stumble’).

